(105, 1, 105, '<p>List of Products under Conditional Export:</p><ol><li>Urea Fertilizer: Urea fertilizer produced in all factories except KAFCO can be exported with the approval of the Ministry of Industries;</li><li>Entertainment programs, music, drama, films, documentary films etc. can be exported in the form of audio cassettes, video cassettes, CDs, DVDs etc. subject to ?no objection? from the Ministry of Information;</li><li>Petroleum and petroleum products produced from natural gas (such as naphtha, furnace oil, bitumen, condensate, MTT and MS) can be exported under ?no objection? from the Energy and Mineral Resources Division. However, lubricating oil can be exported unconditionally under intimation to the Energy and Mineral Resources Division about the amount of export;</li><li>Chemical products enlisted in schedules 1, 2, 3 of Chemical Weapons (Prohibition) Act, 2006 will be either export prohibited or exportable as per the provision of section-9 of the Act;</li><li>Sugar;</li><li>Hilsha fish;</li><li>Aromatic rice;</li><li>Ministry of Commerce will issue export permit for raw hides of crocodiles produced on a commercial basis in private or joint venture farms, subject to approval/no objection from Ministry of Environment and Forest.&nbsp;</li></ol><p>[Ref: Annex-2 of Export Policy 2015-18]</p>', 0, '', 1464235726, '2016-05-26 04:08:46'),
(106, 1, 106, '<p>Diplomats working in Bangladesh are entitled to buy goods under bond facility if they have received exemption certificates from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.&nbsp;</p><p>On the other hand, privileged persons need to obtain passbooks from Customs to buy duty free items. The benefits to be enjoyed by the privileged persons are laid down in the SRO no. 237-Law/2003/2015/Cus, dated 02/08/2003.</p>', 0, '', 1464235771, '2016-05-26 04:09:31'),
(107, 1, 107, '<p>Privileged persons are defined under the SRO no. 237-Law/2003/2015/Cus, dated 02/08/2003. As per Rule 2(d) of the said SRO, a ?Privileged person? means a non-Bangladeshi official working in Bangladesh under:</p><p>(i) the United Nations or an organisation thereunder or a non-Bangladeshi expert performing functions in Bangladesh on behalf of the United nations or an organization thereunder and holding United Nations laissez passer;</p><p>(ii) an International Organization; and</p><p>(iii) a Development Partner of Bangladesh.?</p>', 0, '', 1464235796, '2016-05-26 04:09:56'),
(108, 1, 108, '<p>Benefits enjoyed by the privileged persons are elaborated in the SRO no. 237-Law/2003/2015/Cus, dated 02/08/2003. As per Rule 3 of the said SRO, a privileged person is entitled to import free of customs duties-</p><p>a) articles of foodstuff, medicines and other consumable stores of the value specified in the schedule;</p><p>b) alcoholic beverage, liquor and tobacco of the value specified in the schedule;</p><p>Provided that, the articles under clause (a) and clause (b) may be imported by a privileged person at a time for a maximum of three months quota as specified in the schedule.</p><p>Under Rule 3, a privileged person is also entitled to import free of customs duties,-</p><p>(a) articles for personal use and household effects, if his or her continuous stay in Bangladesh is expected to be not less than six months and such import shall be limited to a maximum Cost, Insurance and Freight (CIF) value of taka fifty thousand for the first year and shall be imported within the period of six months from the date of his or her first arrival in Bangladesh and this period may, on satisfactory grounds, be extended by another period of three months by the commissioner of customs concerned and by the National Board of Revenue for such further period as it may deem fit; and&nbsp;</p><p>(b) after expiry of the period of one year of continuous stay in Bangladesh, articles of personal use and household effects up to the Cost Insurance and Freight (CIF) value of taka fifteen thousand per year for the next two years.</p><p>A privileged person is also entitled to import free of customs duties a motor car for his or her personal and family use, if his or her continuous stay in Bangladesh is expected to be not less than one year and in such case the motor car, if any, shall be imported within six months from the date of his or her first arrival in Bangladesh.</p>', 0, '', 1464235836, '2016-05-26 04:10:36'),
(109, 1, 109, '<p>Purchase of consumable articles from a diplomatic bonded warehouse are elaborated in the SRO no. 237-Law/2003/2015/Cus, dated 02/08/2003. As per Rule 4 of the said SRO, a privileged person may purchase.-</p><p><b>(a) following goods from the diplomatic bonded warehouse of the Bangladesh Parjatan Corporation;</b></p><p>(i) alcoholic beverage and liquor,</p><p>(ii) tobacco,</p><p>(iii) articles of foodstuff,</p><p>(iv) medicine &nbsp;other consumable stores; and&nbsp;</p><p><b>(b) following goods from all other diplomatic bonded warehouses;</b></p><p>(i) alcoholic beverage and liquor,</p><p>(ii) tobacco,</p>', 0, '', 1464235872, '2016-05-26 04:11:12'),
(110, 1, 110, '<p>Yes.&nbsp;</p><p>According to the provisions of the Privileged Persons (Customs Procedures) Rules, 2003, a privileged person is entitled to import free of Customs duties a motor car for his or her personal and family use, if his or her continuous stay in Bangladesh is expected to be not less than one year; in such case the motor car, if any, shall be imported within six months from the date of his or her first arrival in Bangladesh.</p>', 0, '', 1464235885, '2016-05-26 04:11:25'),
(111, 1, 111, '<p>Conditions for import and purchase of goods by privileged persons are elaborated in the SRO no. 237-Law/2003/2015/Cus, dated 02/08/2003. As per Rule 5 of the said SRO, the following conditions will be applicable for such import or purchase:&nbsp;</p><p>(1) The total value of alcoholic beverage, liquor, tobacco, articles of foodstuff, medicine and other consumable stores, either imported or purchased from the diplomatic bonded warehouses, shall not exceed the value mentioned in the Schedule below:</p><table class=\"table table-bordered\">\r\n    <tbody><tr>\r\n        <th>Particular of good</th>\r\n        <th>Monthly entitlement of a privileged person or of each member of his or her family</th>\r\n        <th>Conditions of Import and Purchase</th>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr>\r\n        <td>1</td>\r\n        <td>2</td>\r\n        <td>3</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr>\r\n        <td>Articles of foodstuff, medicine and other consumable stores.</td>\r\n        <td>Up to a CIF value of US $ 60.00</td>\r\n        <td>The total value of goods either imported on a duty-free basis or purchased from the diplomatic bonded warehouse of Bangladesh Parjatan Corporation by a privileged person shall not exceed the value mentioned in column 2.</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr>\r\n        <td>Alcoholic Beverage, liquor and tobacco.</td>\r\n        <td>Up to a CIF value of US $ 100.00</td>\r\n        <td>The total value of goods either imported on a duty-free basis or purchased from any type of diplomatic bonded warehouse by a privileged person shall not exceed the value mentioned in column 2.</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n</tbody></table>\r\n<p>(2) Children below the age of 18 (eighteen) years shall not be entitled to enjoy the quota for alcoholic beverage, liquor and tobacco mentioned in the Schedule.</p>', 0, '', 1464236181, '2016-05-26 04:16:21'),
(112, 1, 112, '<p>The procedure for disposal of vehicles and durable/semi-durable goods imported by diplomatic missions, diplomats, privileged organizations and persons is elaborated in the NBR Standing Order no. 100/2000/Customs, dated 25/07/2000. &nbsp;According to provision no. 3 of the Standing Order, these will be disposed of in any of the following manners:&nbsp;</p><p>(a) Vehicles, durable or semi-durable goods imported without payment of duties and taxes may be re-exported with permission from the Commissioner through whose jurisdiction the goods were imported.</p><p>(b) A diplomatic mission/diplomat/privileged organization or person may sell/transfer such goods without payment of duties and taxes only to another diplomatic mission/diplomat/privileged organization or person with prior permission from the National Board of Revenue (NBR).&nbsp;</p><p>(c) A diplomatic mission/diplomat/privileged organization or person may sell such goods to any non-privileged organization/person on payment of duties and taxes either on expiry of 3 (three) years or on completion of assignment in Bangladesh.&nbsp;</p><p>(d) the aforesaid vehicles/durable or semi-durable goods may be sold/ transferred by diplomatic missions/diplomats only after obtaining a certificate from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Government of Bangladesh. A copy of the said certificate shall be endorsed to the Commissioner of Customs who would make necessary assessment and realize duties and taxes, if applicable. The privileged person/organization concerned shall directly apply to the Commissioner for permission with a copy to the NBR.&nbsp;</p><p>(e) Such vehicles, durable and semi-durable goods may be sold through sealed tender provided, in case of a vehicle, it has been used for at least 08 (eight) years and, in case of other durables/semi-durables, such goods have been used for at least 05 (five) years in Bangladesh.</p>', 0, '', 1464236204, '2016-05-26 04:16:44'),
(113, 1, 113, '<p>The following documents will be required for the export of live pets:</p><ol><li>No objection Certificate (NOC) from the Bangladesh government?s Department of Livestock. To apply to the Department of Livestock, a copy of a valid health certificate and vaccination records have to be enclosed.&nbsp;</li><li>No Objection Certificate (NOC) from the Ministry of Foreign affairs. This permission is only required for the employees of foreign embassies in Bangladesh. Private citizens do not require this permission. (a copy of a valid health certificate and vaccination records will be required for applying to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs)</li><li>Permission/NOC of the Office of the Chief Controller of Imports and Exports (CCI&amp;E). A copy of the health certificate and vaccination records will have to be attached along with the application.</li></ol>', 0, '', 1464236240, '2016-05-26 04:17:20'),
(114, 1, 114, '<p>As per the conditions laid down in Part A under Annexure 1 of the Import Policy Order, 2015-2018, a motor car of any cylinder capacity (C.C.) or a microbus, minibus, jeep or &nbsp;any other vehicle or tractor belonging to HS Heading 87.01 to 87.04 will not be importable if it is more than five years old . This implies that vehicles will not be more than 5 years old in the case of shipment.&nbsp;</p><p>Such old vehicles will be importable only from the country of its origin (manufacture). In such case, a certificate containing age, model number and chassis number of the old car will have to be submitted to the Customs authority from Japan Auto Appraisal Institute (JAAI) in case of import of cars from Japan and from the recognized Automobile Association in case of import of old cars from other countries.</p><p>For determining date or age of the imported old car, the date or age will be calculated from the first day of the next year of manufacture of chassis. No old car or vehicle will be importable from a country which do not publish chassis book.</p><p>No car will be importable without seat belt. Wind shield glass and window glasses on both sides of driving seat must be transparent so that inside of the car is visible.&nbsp;</p><p>Old Taxicab will be importable only if it has an engine capacity of 1500 or more, and is less than 3 years old. In such case, other conditions laid down in Part A of Annexure 1 of the Import Policy Order will also have to be fulfilled.</p><p>Note: For more information, please contact the Ministry of Commerce.</p>', 0, '', 1464236270, '2016-05-26 04:17:50'),
(115, 1, 115, '<p>For the purpose of determining importability, the process for determining the age of imported old/used/reconditioned motor vehicles of Headings 8701 to 8704 is elaborated in Part A under Annexure 1 of the Import Policy Order, 2015-2018. &nbsp;No such vehicle will be importable if it is more than five years old. For determining the date or age of such motor vehicle, the date or age will be calculated from the first day of the next year of manufacture of chassis.</p><p>Note: For more information, please contact the Ministry of Commerce.</p>', 0, '', 1464236285, '2016-05-26 04:18:05'),
(116, 1, 116, '<p>No.</p><p>One cannot import a vehicle of 2010 in 2016. If the chassis of a car is manufactured in 2010, the age of the old car will be calculated from January 01, 2011 and it will be more than 5 years old if it is shipped from the exporting country on or after 01 January 2016. &nbsp;However, the car/vehicle will remain importable if it is shipped within 31 December, 2015.</p><p>Note: For more information, please contact the Ministry of Commerce.</p>', 0, '', 1464236296, '2016-05-26 04:18:16'),
(117, 1, 117, '<p>As per the conditions laid down in Part A under Annexure 1 of the Import Policy Order, 2015-2018, old vehicles will not be importable from any third country.&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">However, old vehicles that were in personal use abroad and will be in personal use after importation can be imported from a third country. In such cases, certificate of registration &amp; certificate of cancellation of registration (from the country of use) will have to be submitted to the customs authority.&nbsp;</span><br></p><p>Note: For more information, please contact the Ministry of Commerce.</p>', 0, '', 1464236310, '2016-05-26 04:18:30'),
(118, 1, 118, '<p>No.&nbsp;</p><p>A person is not allowed to import painted (i.e. with final colour) bus, truck, minibus, Jeep, motor car, tractor and motor cycle in CKD condition. Only final coating may be allowed. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>(Reference: NBR Nothi no. 9(4) Cus-1/93/(Part-1)/162/(1-9) date- 09-04-1997 and NBR nothi no 1(8) Shu:Nii: O Baa:/2007/304 date- 04/06/2015)</p>', 0, '', 1464236320, '2016-05-26 04:18:40'),
(119, 1, 119, '<p>In the case where an Intellectual Property (IP) rights holder (objector) lodges a Notice of Objection, Customs will seize any goods that infringes a copyright or a registered trade mark. Both the importer and the rights holder will be notified of the seizure. Under section 15 of the Customs Act, 1969, import of such goods are prohibited.&nbsp;</p><p>Unless the rights holder commences legal proceedings with the Court, Customs will conduct proceedings under section 156(1) (9) of the Customs Act.</p>', 0, '', 1464236353, '2016-05-26 04:19:13'),
(120, 1, 120, '<p>In this case, penalty would be imposed on the basis of the value of the goods with respect to which misdeclaration has been made or offence has taken place. The adjudicating officer, will however, be selected on the value of the total consignment.&nbsp;</p><p>[Reference: (a) column 14 of the Table under Section 156(1); (b) NBR nothi no. 10(1)Cus-1/91/268(1) date-12/08/1999]</p><p>Note: For more information, please contact the Ministry of Agriculture.</p>', 0, '', 1464236415, '2016-05-26 04:20:15'),
(121, 1, 121, '<p><b>(A) </b>According to the Trademarks Act, 2009, trade description markings must be:</p><ul><li>in English</li><li>in prominent and legible characters</li><li>on the main label or brand attached to the goods, in a prominent position and in a way that is as permanent as practicable</li></ul><p>It must include the name of the country where the goods were made or produced. &nbsp;A trade description must also include a true description about the goods. ?True description? signifies a description that is true and accurate about the goods. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><b>(B) </b>Goods with a false trade description must not be imported or exported. A false trade description is one that is likely to mislead the people/users about key characteristics of the good. Examples include the weight, origin, manufacturer, and contents.</p><p>Section 15 of the Customs Act, 1969 prohibits the import of goods having applied thereto a false trade description within the meaning of the Trademarks Act, 2009. &nbsp;If goods with a false trade description is imported, Customs will take appropriate actions as prescribed under serial no. 9 of section 156(1) of the Customs Act, 1969.</p><p>Note: For more information on Part A, please consult the Trademarks Act, 2009.</p>', 0, '', 1464236524, '2016-05-26 04:22:04'),
(122, 1, 122, '<p>Computers are known as automatic data processing machines, and are classifiable under HS Heading 84.71. General import of such computers are not duty free. However, an importer needs to pay only a minimal rate of Customs duty of 2% on computers, computer parts, and computer accessories. Other taxes, such as Supplementary duty (if any) and VAT, are exempted. The NBR offers this facility under the Statutory Regulatory Order (SRO) no. 157-law-/2011/2343/Customs, dated 09 June 2011.</p><p>The SRO also covers computer printers and their parts (HS Heading 84.43), toner/inkjet cartridges (HS Heading 84.43) and ribbons (HS Heading 96.12) for computer, computer parts (HS Heading 84.73), and computer software, magnetic/optical media, flash memory etc. (HS Heading 85.23).&nbsp;</p>', 0, '', 1464236554, '2016-05-26 04:22:34'),
(123, 1, 123, '<p><b>(A)&nbsp;</b></p><p>The relief goods are categorized under SRO no. 61-Law/92/1444/Cus, dated 17/03/2016. Under the SRO, the following goods are exempted from the payment of Customs duty, Value Added Tax and Supplementary duty:</p><ol><li>Food cereals, Edible oils, Biscuits, Tinned foods, Dairy foods, Powdered milk, Baby food, Korbani meat (sacrificial meat) from Saudi Arabia, and Other food items;</li><li>Textiles and textile products, Blankets, Tents, and Household crockeries;</li><li>Medicines, Medical equipment, and Hospital equipment and materials;</li><li>Seeds, Fertilizers, Animals, Insecticides, Fowls and Chickens, Hand-operated pumps, Pipe tractors, Power Tillers and engines of these machinery, Other agricultural machinery and products;</li><li>Tube well items;</li><li>CI Sheet, GP Sheet, BP Sheet, Plastic Sheet, Polythene Sheet, Wood, Cement, Clamps, Screws, and Other building materials;</li><li>Nylon twine, Fishing boat, Tar, and Other items necessary for fishermen and Loomers; and</li><li>School stationery, and Toys.</li></ol><p><b>(B)</b></p><p>SRO no. 61-Law/92/1444/Cus, dated 17/03/2016 has set a number of conditions which need to be fulfilled in order to receive duty free benefits for the above-mentioned relief goods. These include-</p><ol><li>Goods are to be imported in the name of the Government of Bangladesh, Bangladesh Red Crescent Society, any domestic/foreign voluntary organization registered under the NGO Affairs Bureau, or any unregistered local/foreign organization.</li><li>If the Importer is:</li><ul><li>the Government of Bangladesh or the Bangladesh Red Crescent Society, a certificate by an officer not below the rank of Deputy Secretary of the concerned ministry;&nbsp;</li><li>a local/foreign voluntary organization registered under the NGO Affairs Bureau, a certificate by an officer not below the rank of Deputy Secretary of the NGO Affairs Bureau;</li><li>an unregistered local/foreign organization, a certificate by the Secretary of the Ministry of Relief and Rehabilitation;--&nbsp;<span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">must be issued in favor of the concerned Commissioner of Customs that the goods are received as relief materials for distribution free of cost among the destitute/poor people/organizations, &nbsp;and that the goods will not be otherwise sold or used in any other way.</span></li></ul><li><span style=\"line-height: 1.4;\">The organization importing the goods must provide an undertaking addressing the concerned Commissioner of Customs that it will remain liable to pay the assessable duties, VAT and supplementary duties if the goods received are disposed of in any manner other than free distribution.&nbsp;</span></li></ol>', 0, '', 1464236755, '2016-05-26 04:25:55'),
(124, 1, 124, '<p>The National Board of Revenue is currently working on developing the Authorized Economic Operator/ Trusted Traders system in Bangladesh, as part of its customs modernization program. \r\nOnce the AEO system is developed and implemented in Bangladesh, the NBR will be able to share information on the criteria for selection of the AEOs / trusted traders.</p>', 0, '', 1464236818, '2016-05-26 04:26:58'),
(125, 1, 125, '<p>The National Board of Revenue is currently working on developing the Authorized Economic Operator/ Trusted Traders system in Bangladesh, as part of its customs modernization program.&nbsp;</p><p>Once the AEO system is developed and implemented in Bangladesh, the NBR will be able to share information on the potential benefits to be offered to the AEOs /trusted traders.</p>', 0, '', 1464236956, '2016-05-26 04:29:16'),
(126, 1, 126, '<p>The National Board of Revenue is currently working on developing the Authorized Economic Operator/ Trusted Traders system in Bangladesh, as part of its customs modernization program.&nbsp;</p><p>Once the AEO system is developed and implemented in Bangladesh, the NBR will be able to share the information on whether the SMEs will be eligible to apply for an AEO status.</p>', 0, '', 1464236966, '2016-05-26 04:29:26'),
(127, 1, 127, '<p>Courier service providers are regulated by the Ministry of Post and Telecommunications.</p><p>Customs deals with the processing of imports and exports of the courier consignments. Such courier consignments are currently processed through ASYCUDA WORLD. However, courier cargos containing documents only are processed manually irrespective of weight, and are cleared by respective courier service providers through their designated C&amp;F agents.</p>', 0, '', 1464237005, '2016-05-26 04:30:05'),
(128, 1, 128, '<p>Yes.</p><p>Rewards/prizes won/gained by any Bangladeshi citizens or organizations as a symbol of success in any recognized international competition are exempted from Customs duties and Value Added Tax subject to the following conditions:</p><ol><li>Vehicles/cars, televisions, refrigerators, air conditioners or any other similar consumer durables will not enjoy this duty free facility</li><li>A certificate (in the prescribed form) from the concerned official of the Ministry/Division has to be submitted to the concerned Customs Station for each consignment.</li><li>The rewards/prizes will not be sold or transferred without prior permission from the NBR and payment of applicable duties and taxes. &nbsp;</li></ol><p>[Reference: SRO 105-AIN/97/1703/Shulka, dated: 03 April, 1997).&nbsp;</p>', 0, '', 1464237029, '2016-05-26 04:30:29'),
(129, 1, 129, '<p>If the shipment condition states, say for example, CIF Chicago, it means that the exporter will have to bear all costs (costs, insurance and freight) that are incurred in order for the cargo to reach Chicago (its port of destination).<br></p>', 0, '', 1464237046, '2016-05-26 04:30:46'),
(130, 3, 130, '<p>Each passenger is entitled duty free import of gold ornaments not exceeding 100 grams.</p><p>Please read guidelines as per:<a href=\" http://bangladeshcustoms.gov.bd/beta/relevant/baggage_rules\" target=\"_blank\"> http://bangladeshcustoms.gov.bd/beta/relevant/baggage_rules</a></p><p><br></p>', 0, '', 1479780499, '2016-11-22 02:08:19'),
